## Dingo

Dingoes are wild dogs native to Australia. They're medium-sized, with slim, strong bodies built for running. Their fur can be ginger, black and tan, or creamy white. Dingoes are related to New Guinea singing dogs and split from other dogs thousands of years ago.

They live in packs, usually with a mom, dad, their puppies, and sometimes older siblings.
